						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab standing in front of the Siddhēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Bhuvanaikamalla (Sōmēśvara II)—A.D. 1074.</p>						

						<p>The record is badly damaged and worn out. It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 995, Ānanda, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti,</hi> the other details being lost. It corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1074 December 24,</hi> the Śaka year being 996 and not 995. </p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to register a gift of oil and income from certain taxes. It mentions the Four Hundred Mahājanas and refers to Telligas and Bāḻagaṇa.</p>						

						</summary>
